  "text": "The surgical treatment initially described in the literature was ligation of the left coronary artery [CITATION_1] . Since then, several other surgical approaches have been described [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , such as subclavian-to-left coronary artery anastomosis, direct re-implantation of the anomalous artery to the aorta, or Takeuchi repair (with an intra-pulmonary baffle). Currently, re-establishment of the dual coronary system is considered the best approach [CITATION_4] .",
